# 1. 新しい出会い

Ena: <How does it look, Amia? Does it work with what we talked about...?>
Mizuki: <Yeah, I think so! Have K see it later too. Yuki's got club activities so we can try sending it to her tonight.>
Ena: <Okay, that works.>
Ena: (Mizuki seems fine as far as I can tell. Was I just seeing things before? But...)
Ena: <Um, Amia... Can I ask you something...?>
Mizuki: <Hm? What's up?>
Ena: <It's about the mystery tour you took us on the other day...>
Mizuki: <Yeah, that was so much fun! It was so cute how you just completely passed out once you got on the train too, Enanan♪>
Ena: <Do you know how tired we all were after that?! Don't think that's how I usually sleep either... Anyways, that's not what I want to ask you about...>
Ena: <After we saw those cherry blossoms together, did something happen? You seem a little different, you know...?>
Mizuki: <Huh? Really? I feel fine.>
Ena: <But...>
Kanade: <Sorry I'm late. I've been working but just forgot to log in.>
Mizuki: <Hey, K! We were just talking about the illustrations and stuff we're gonna use for the video, right, Enanan?>
Ena: <Oh, um... Y-Yeah. Let me send them over...>
Ena: *Sigh*...
Ena: (I couldn't get anything out of Mizuki. Something feels off, but at the same time, everything seems fine...)
Ena: (No, making that kind of face means something has to be up...)
Ena: (Mizuki's the one that always says that we should go out and celebrate after we finish making a song, but that hasn't been the case lately...)
Ena: (What if it's something that isn't easy to talk about...? But Mizuki doesn't seem like the type to hide anything from anyone...)
Ena: (Even when I do ask, I never get any answers so... What am I supposed to do?)
Ena: Ugh! This is so frustrating!!
Ena: (Hm? My phone's ringing... Airi...?)
Ena: <Hi, Airi. What's up?>
Airi: <Sorry to call you like this all the sudden. My lesson for this weekend got cancelled, so I thought that maybe we could go out and do something together. What do you think?>
Airi: <There's also someone I want to introduce you to. Her name's Shizuku Hinomori and we're in the same idol group...>
Ena: <What?! Shizuku Hinomori as in the girl you're always talking about...? The one from that video you were in the other day...?>
Airi: <Yeah, her! I mentioned you to her today and she's sort of looking forward to meeting you now.>
Ena: <She is...? But sorry, I might not be up for that just yet....>
Airi: <Huh? What's wrong? Did something happen? Another fight with your dad...?>
Ena: <No, there's just something that's been bothering me a little...>
Airi: <Really? Like what...? Well, I guess we all have days like that...>
Airi: <Also, you'll start gaining weight if you stay inside too long. It's important to go outside and get a breath of fresh air every so often, you know?>
Ena: <...!>
Airi: <But I won't force you into doing anything. When you feel like chatting or meeting up, just let me know, okay?>
Ena: <Maybe I should go...>
Ena: <You're right about me not going out much lately, Airi. This thing will probably just keep bothering me unless I actually do something about it.>
Airi: <Hehe. Then it's settled!>
Ena: <But no more insinuations regarding my weight, okay?>
Airi: <Yeah, yeah, I'll stop. Anyways, we'll talk again after I hash out the details, like when to meet and stuff.>
Ena: <Okay. Bye.>
Ena: Airi called at the perfect time. Alright, I'm gonna shop 'til I drop this weekend...!
Airi: Ena, over here! I was worried about meeting up this early, but I'm glad you woke up on time.
Ena: Hehehe. I told Akito yesterday to wake me up this morning!
Airi: You're still using your little brother as a human alarm clock? I can't help but feel sorry for him...
Ena: By the way, is Hinomori not here yet?
Airi: No, not yet. She usually wakes up on time, but she gets lost pretty easily...
Ena: Lost? She's not a little kid, so I can't imagine...
Shizuku: I'm sorry for being so late, you two...!
Airi: Shizuku! We were just talking about you. Did something happen?
Shizuku: Actually, the bus I was on was stuck in traffic. I tried to send you a message, but I couldn't since the screen on my phone just kept spinning around...
Ena: Spinning around...?
Shizuku: Oh...! Are you Shinonome?
Shizuku: My name's Shizuku Hinomori. It's so nice to finally meet you. Airi's been telling me all about you.
Ena: Y-Yes, I'm Ena Shinonome. It's nice to meet you too, Hinomori.
Ena: (Sh-She's so pretty... She really is like someone you see in a magazine but... Hm?)
Ena: Wait, are you not wearing any make-up...?
Shizuku: Hm? Oh, no I'm not. But I put on some lip gloss and sunscreen since Airi said it might be a good idea to.
Ena: What?! Just that?! H-How can anyone naturally look this good...?!
Airi: Yeah, a lot of people have the same reaction...
Shizuku: Is something the matter? Oh, is there something on my face?
Ena: N-N-No! It's nothing!
Ena: (Airi said that there's a part of her that's a bit of an airhead and I sort of noticed that in their video too...)
Ena: (But is she more of an airhead than I realize...?)
Airi: Anyways, Shizuku's finally here, so let's get down to some shopping!
Airi: That was so much fun! I even got some cute clothes thanks to you, Ena♪
Shizuku: Yes, you even helped me pick out some cosmetics as well. I usually have such a difficult time finding anything that suits me...
Ena: Don't worry about it. It was nothing, really.
Ena: I got my hands on some things I wanted too. I'll take some pics of them later♪
Airi: I'm glad that you seem to feel a little better too.
Ena: Yeah, I'm glad I came today.
Shizuku: Oh, was there something wrong?
Ena: No, not really wrong... It's just that there was something bothering me lately and I thought I should go out instead of staying cooped up inside all day.
Shizuku: I see...
Shizuku: Would it be alright if I asked what was bothering you, Shinonome...?
Shizuku: You were such a big help to me today, so I'd like to return the favor somehow.
Ena: Huh? But we've been having so much fun. I'd hate to ruin the mood with something like this...
Airi: No, don't worry about that. We were the ones that sort of dragged you out of your house.
Airi: And don't you think you'll feel better by talking about it with someone♪
Ena: Yeah, you're probably right...
Ena: This isn't actually about me but...
Airi: I see... So you're wondering why this Akiyama's been acting so different lately...
Ena: Yeah. Everything seems normal when we talk, including the upbeat attitude...
Ena: Usually, I'm being the one invited out, but we haven't been hanging out much together lately. We're definitely still friends, but I feel like Mizuki's avoiding me...
Shizuku: I see. That is concerning...
Ena: It is... Every time I ask, Mizuki just laughs it off or dodges the question altogether...
Ena: And that's what's so frustrating about this...!
Ena: Mizuki always asks everyone about how they feel, and I was hoping that I could help if something really is wrong...
Airi: Let me just ask this. Did you say anything that would offend your friend? I sort of can't rule that out with you...
Ena: What? No way!
Shizuku: But if that's so, it could be something that's difficult to talk to you about, Shinonome...
Airi: Yeah, Shizuku might be right. You two being close could be why it's so hard to talk about it.
Ena: Because we're close...? Wait, does that mean I can't do anything about this?
Shizuku: Shinonome...
Shizuku: (She went through the trouble of telling us this and I'd like to be able to help her...)
Shizuku: (But I did the same thing when something was bothering me, so that it wouldn't affect the others around me. Oh, what if...?)
Shizuku: What if your friend talked to someone less personally involved, Shinonome? Would that make things easier?
Ena: Less involved?
Shizuku: For example, Airi and myself.
Shizuku: What if the four of us, Akiyama included, went on a little outing together? It could help make things easier for the two of you.
Ena: I appreciate the idea, but would it really work...?
Airi: I'm not sure either. It may not solve everything on its own, but it could give you a better idea of what's going on. A change of pace might also do Akiyama some good too, you know?
Ena: That may be true but... Okay, I guess we won't know unless we try...
Ena: But where do we go? We went shopping together just the other day so...
Airi: How about here? I just got a flyer advertising it...
Ena: "A Day Hike in the Highlands"...?
Mizuki: (*Sigh*... Supplementary classes are taking forever today. Our lunch break's almost over too...)
Mizuki: (I guess I'll eat in the classroom. But everyone's still there, so maybe... The rooftop...?)
Rui: Mizuki...?
Mizuki: Huh?! Rui?!
Rui: My apologies. I didn't mean to surprise you like that. You seemed a little down so I decided to ask...
Mizuki: Haha. Can you tell...? They ran out of the melon bread I was after and I feel a little bummed out. Bad luck, right?
Rui: I see. If you say so...
Nene: Oh, Rui. Can we talk for a minute...?
Mizuki: Looks like you got a visitor! Later, Rui!
Rui: Wait, Mizuki...
Nene: Sorry, did I interrupt your conversation with Akiyama...?
Rui: I can't honestly say no, but you wanted to talk...?
Nene: It's about rehearsing for our next show. Can we discuss a few things?
Rui: Yes, of course.
Rui: ...
